- Approved projects refer to projects with the status 'approved'.; 
- Budget revisions refer to the number of times the budget has been revised, which is stored in the 'budget_revisions' column of the 'budgets' table.; 
- Financial reports exceeding $500 refer to reports with 'financials' greater than 500, as stored in the 'reports' table.

- "approved" refers to the status name of a project; 
- "average allocated budget" refers to the average budget allocated for projects managed by a team member, calculated by summing up the allocated budget for each project and dividing by the number of projects; 
- "$100,000" is the threshold value for the average allocated budget.
